<subSubSection pageId="16" pageNumber="173" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="16.[151,1436,289,602]" pageId="16" pageNumber="173">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,328,325,350]" pageId="16" pageNumber="173">Comments</emphasis>
. This female specimen does not match any described Neotropical 
<taxonomicName box="[1141,1255,326,349]" class="Insecta" family="Agromyzidae" genus="Liriomyza" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="16" pageNumber="173" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[1141,1255,326,349]" italics="true" pageId="16" pageNumber="173">Liriomyza</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
species and is definitely distinct from 
<taxonomicName box="[433,547,362,385]" class="Insecta" family="Agromyzidae" genus="Liriomyza" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="16" pageNumber="173" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[433,547,362,385]" italics="true" pageId="16" pageNumber="173">Liriomyza</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
sp. A described above. Because no males are available the species is not described here, but the diagnostic characters include: orbit almost completely yellow with upper orbit pale brown near eye margin; vte on pale brown, vti on yellow ground; hind margin of eye black on upper half; palpus yellow; antenna with scape yellow, pedicel mostly brown, first flagellomere yellowish basally and brown apically; mesonotum dark to margin of scutellum with hind corners slightly paler brown; anepisternum and katepisternum mostly dark except for narrow upper margin; 
<number box="[662,676,542,566]" pageId="16" pageNumber="173" value="3.0">3</number>
+ 
<number box="[695,706,542,566]" pageId="16" pageNumber="173" value="1.0">1</number>
dc; acr in 
<number box="[824,838,542,566]" pageId="16" pageNumber="173" value="4.0">4</number>
irregular rows; fore coxa mostly brown but narrowly yellow apically; femora mostly brown with some yellow striations; wing length 
<quantity box="[1049,1138,577,601]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="2.1" pageId="16" pageNumber="173" unit="mm" value="2.1">2.1 mm</quantity>
.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
